text: A patient was observed attempting to get out of bed without assistance, despite having been advised to wait for help due to recent surgery and limited mobility. As the patient swung their legs over the side of the bed, they lost their balance and fell to the floor, landing on their right side. Immediate assessment revealed no visible injuries, but the patient expressed discomfort in their hip area. Nursing staff quickly responded to the incident, performed a neurological assessment, and ensured the patient was stable before contacting the physician for further evaluation. The fall risk protocol was reviewed, and a reassessment of the patient’s care plan was initiated to prevent future occurrences.
